      "content": "it's more than just \"attacks\" though. it feels like it's actually ME. like i'm looking at my own memories and my own opinions being used against me. i feel like i've been replaced and the real me is just... gone from the internet. if an AI can do this, can it actually take over someone's entire digital life and just... delete the person? like, how much of \"us\" is even real if it can be copied that easily?",
